604
00:40:10,661 --> 00:40:12,996
Yes. I've got all his audios.

605
00:40:51,076 --> 00:40:55,038
Mum, did you always know
I was going to be a vegetarian?

606
00:40:55,664 --> 00:40:56,915
Yeah, of course I did.

607
00:40:57,082 --> 00:41:00,627
I didn't decide on the spur of the moment
'cause we ran out of sausages.

608
00:41:00,711 --> 00:41:03,088
Did you ask me if I wanted
to be a vegetarian?

609
00:41:03,213 --> 00:41:05,048
What, when you were born?

610
00:41:05,257 --> 00:41:07,467
I do the cooking and I
don't want to cook meat.

611
00:41:07,551 --> 00:41:10,053
You have to eat what I eat.

612
00:41:11,346 --> 00:41:13,974
But you don't let me go
to McDonald's, either.

613
00:41:14,516 --> 00:41:17,060
Is this premature teenage rebellion?

614
00:41:17,686 --> 00:41:20,022
I can't stop you from going to McDonald's.

615
00:41:20,105 --> 00:41:22,733
I'd just be disappointed if you did.

616
00:41:25,694 --> 00:41:28,947
Don't worry, Mum.
I won't go to McDonald's.

617
00:41:32,618 --> 00:41:37,039
After a few visits, Will seemed to think
he had to ask me serious questions.

618
00:41:37,122 --> 00:41:41,210
But I knew he really wanted to watch
Warrior Princess.

619
00:41:41,293 --> 00:41:43,170
So, how's it going at home then?

620
00:41:43,253 --> 00:41:45,923
- You mean my mum?
- Yeah.

621
00:41:46,340 --> 00:41:48,383
She's all right, thanks.

622
00:41:51,637 --> 00:41:54,097
I mean, you know, she's....

623
00:41:55,766 --> 00:41:59,520
Yeah, I know. No, nothing like that.

624
00:42:03,398 --> 00:42:05,484
Does it still bother you, then?

625
00:42:06,568 --> 00:42:08,028
Does it bother me?

626
00:42:09,905 --> 00:42:11,490
Are you decent?

627
00:42:16,036 --> 00:42:17,704
Every single day.

628
00:42:17,913 --> 00:42:20,374
That's why I come here,
instead of going home.

629
00:42:20,541 --> 00:42:23,210
A bit. When I think about it.

630
00:42:25,796 --> 00:42:27,506
Fucking hell.

631
00:42:30,843 --> 00:42:34,638
I don't know why he swore like that,
but it made me feel better.

632
00:42:35,597 --> 00:42:39,142
It made me feel like I wasn't
being pathetic to get so scared.

633
00:42:42,646 --> 00:42:45,607
I wouldn't make the mistake of asking
about Fiona again.

634
00:42:45,691 --> 00:42:47,484
Marcus was clearly screwed up about it...

635
00:42:47,568 --> 00:42:51,488
and unfortunately I couldn't think
of anything to say that'd be of any value.

636
00:42:51,572 --> 00:42:54,199
Next time he could talk to Suzie,
or a counselor...

637
00:42:54,324 --> 00:42:57,411
or anybody capable
of something more than an obscenity.

638
00:42:57,494 --> 00:42:59,705
Shit! It can't be.

639
00:43:03,000 --> 00:43:05,127
November-the-sodding-19.

