644
00:43:23,812 --> 00:43:27,441
You know, he wrote one crap song
that turned out to be a massive hit...

645
00:43:27,524 --> 00:43:31,320
and then spent the rest of his life
trying to write a better one.

646
00:43:31,403 --> 00:43:33,363
Do you ever want to write songs like him?

647
00:43:33,447 --> 00:43:35,657
Is that what the guitar's for?

648
00:43:37,159 --> 00:43:38,243
No.

649
00:43:39,620 --> 00:43:42,122
So, that's just there to look cool.

650
00:43:42,789 --> 00:43:43,707
Yeah.

651
00:43:47,377 --> 00:43:49,713
I like Santa's Super Sleigh.

652
00:44:06,730 --> 00:44:09,816
Madonna! Come here!
We've got something.

653
00:44:10,108 --> 00:44:12,486
He's getting away, look!
Hurry up!

654
00:44:12,653 --> 00:44:16,198
On Pet Rescue today,
the clever stoat keeps everyone...

655
00:44:16,281 --> 00:44:18,575
on their toes in Somerset.

656
00:44:44,351 --> 00:44:45,727
Hey!

657
00:44:45,936 --> 00:44:47,896
What are you doing?
Who are you?

658
00:44:47,980 --> 00:44:49,147
Who am I?

659
00:44:49,314 --> 00:44:53,443
Bugger off, that's who I am!
Go on, piss off!

660
00:44:55,445 --> 00:44:56,989
Who were they, then?

661
00:44:57,072 --> 00:44:58,407
Who?

662
00:44:58,490 --> 00:44:59,533
What do you mean, "Who?"

663
00:44:59,616 --> 00:45:02,494
The ones
trying to embed sweets into your skull.

664
00:45:02,619 --> 00:45:03,662
Oh, them.

665
00:45:03,745 --> 00:45:07,666
They're just a couple of older kids.
They started following me after school.

666
00:45:07,749 --> 00:45:09,418
Does this happen often?

667
00:45:09,501 --> 00:45:12,212
They never chucked sweets before,
they just thought of that.

668
00:45:12,296 --> 00:45:15,841
I'm not talking about the sweets.
The kids trying to kill you.

669
00:45:15,924 --> 00:45:18,260
Yeah, they give me a hard time.

670
00:45:18,468 --> 00:45:21,972
You know, about my hair,
and my clothes and singing and stuff.

671
00:45:22,097 --> 00:45:23,557
And what? And singing?

672
00:45:24,975 --> 00:45:27,811
Sometimes I sing out loud without noticing.

673
00:45:28,604 --> 00:45:30,230
That's not a brilliant idea, is it?

674
00:45:30,314 --> 00:45:34,359
I said I did it without noticing, didn't I?
It just happens!

675
00:45:34,735 --> 00:45:38,488
I'm not going to do it on purpose, am I?
I'm not stupid, you know.

676
00:45:38,614 --> 00:45:42,784
My advice is to keep out of people's way.
Try to make yourself invisible.

677
00:45:42,868 --> 00:45:44,286
How can I be invisible?

678
00:45:44,369 --> 00:45:46,663
One machine in your kitchen
is an invisible machine?

679
00:45:46,747 --> 00:45:48,457
I don't think so.

680
00:45:50,667 --> 00:45:53,545
I just try not to think of it, that's all.

681
00:45:54,755 --> 00:45:58,217
It happens, and I wish it didn't,
but that's life, isn't it?

682
00:46:00,427 --> 00:46:02,971
There's nothing I can do about it.

683
00:46:06,391 --> 00:46:07,476
No.

684
00:46:09,353 --> 00:46:12,481
There is something we can
do about it, Marcus.

685
00:46:13,232 --> 00:46:14,816
You're coming with me.

686
00:46:14,900 --> 00:46:18,487
I was worried he was going to take me
to the headmistress' office.

687
00:46:20,030 --> 00:46:21,949
But instead he took me shopping.

688
00:46:22,032 --> 00:46:23,242
I don't get it.

689
00:46:23,325 --> 00:46:24,993
We're starting with your feet.

690
00:46:25,077 --> 00:46:29,081
I can't make you invisible,
but I can make you blend in with the crowd.

691
00:46:29,915 --> 00:46:33,377
