boy temporarily happy.

708
00:47:32,060 --> 00:47:34,229
And there wasn't anything
in it for me at all.

709
00:47:34,313 --> 00:47:36,398
I didn't even want to shag his mum.

710
00:47:47,659 --> 00:47:50,412
Marcus! What happened to your shoes?

711
00:47:50,662 --> 00:47:52,331
They stole them.

712
00:48:02,424 --> 00:48:04,426
Why would anyone want to steal your shoes?

713
00:48:04,510 --> 00:48:06,762
I could see I had to tell the truth.

714
00:48:06,845 --> 00:48:09,848
The problem was, the truth would
lead to a lot more questions.

715
00:48:09,973 --> 00:48:11,517
They were nice ones.

716
00:48:11,600 --> 00:48:13,977
They were just ordinary brown lace-ups.

717
00:48:14,061 --> 00:48:17,231
No, they weren't. They
were cool new trainers.

718
00:48:17,397 --> 00:48:19,733
Where did you get cool new trainers?

719
00:48:19,816 --> 00:48:21,568
She had loads more questions.

720
00:48:21,652 --> 00:48:23,445
Will bought them for me.

721
00:48:25,113 --> 00:48:26,114
Will?

722
00:48:27,324 --> 00:48:29,952
- The guy who took us to lunch?
- Yeah.

723
00:48:30,327 --> 00:48:32,287
He's sort of become my friend.

724
00:48:32,829 --> 00:48:34,540
He's sort of become your friend?

725
00:48:34,623 --> 00:48:37,125
She kept repeating
the last thing I said.

726
00:48:37,209 --> 00:48:38,877
Except she shouted it.

727
00:48:39,169 --> 00:48:41,463
I go round to his place after school.

728
00:48:41,547 --> 00:48:44,216
You go round to his place after school!

729
00:48:44,299 --> 00:48:48,095
- You see, he doesn't really have a kid.
