730
00:48:48,178 --> 00:48:50,305
Can I play computer games now?

731
00:48:50,556 --> 00:48:51,598
Where does he live?

732
00:48:51,723 --> 00:48:54,518
He's not there at the moment.
He's out to dinner.

733
00:48:56,603 --> 00:48:59,606
Christine had asked me to dinner
for a pep talk.

734
00:48:59,731 --> 00:49:03,110
You will end up childless and alone.

735
00:49:03,193 --> 00:49:05,237
Both fingers crossed, yeah.

736
00:49:07,155 --> 00:49:08,657
You must have a lot of courage.

737
00:49:08,740 --> 00:49:10,742
Why is that, Christine?

738
00:49:11,410 --> 00:49:14,872
Most people need something in their lives
to keep them afloat...

739
00:49:14,997 --> 00:49:17,958
and you have absolutely nothing.

740
00:49:18,750 --> 00:49:20,669
Doesn't that scare you?

741
00:49:21,378 --> 00:49:23,338
Do you know what you want?

742
00:49:24,923 --> 00:49:26,508
Yes, I do. I'll have the steak...

743
00:49:26,592 --> 00:49:30,137
What the hell are these little
after-school tea parties about?

744
00:49:30,637 --> 00:49:32,598
Hi. Sorry? What did you say?

745
00:49:32,681 --> 00:49:36,810
I was just wondering why a single,
childless man would want to hang out...

